{"questionId":"21954","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A manufacturer of chocolates produces them in individual packets, claiming to have an&nbsp;average of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>85</mn></math> chocolates per packet.</p>\n<p>Talha bought <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math> of these packets in order to check the manufacturer’s claim.</p>\n<p>Given that the number of individual chocolates is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>, Talha found that, from his <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math> packets,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Σ</mtext><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2506</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Σ</mtext><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>209</mn><mo> </mo><mn>738</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>95</mn><mo>%</mo></math> confidence interval for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi></math>. You may assume that all conditions for a&nbsp;confidence interval have been met.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>84</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1405</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>84</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9261</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21954","referenceCode":"21M.1.AHL.TZ2.10c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find a 95% confidence interval for μ. You may assume that all conditions for a confidence interval have been met.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Linear transformation of a single RV, E(X) and VAR(X), unbiased estimators","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.16—Confidence intervals"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}